original_text_en:
A cyclist starts from point A towards point B and arrives at point B 2 hours later. At that time, another person (B) starts walking from point A towards point B. When B has walked for 2 hours, A reaches point B, and B is then 32 kilometers away from point B.

A rests at point B for 2 hours and 30 minutes before returning along the same route. After 1 hour of cycling back, A meets B who is still walking towards point B. The question asks: How many kilometers is B away from point B at that moment?

**Word-for-word translation:**

-甲 (A) 騎車 (cycling) 自A地 (from point A) 向B地 (towards point B) 駛去 (starts), 2小時後 (after 2 hours), 乙 (B) 步行 (walking) 由A地 (from point A) 向B地 (towards point B) 走去 (starts), 乙走出2小時後 (when B has walked for 2 hours), 甲到B地 (A arrives at point B), 此時乙距B地32公里 (at that moment, B is 32 kilometers away from point B);
-甲在B地休息2小時30分鐘 (A rests at point B for 2 hours and 30 minutes) 又原路返回 (then returns along the same route), 經過1小時與一直步行向B地走的乙相遇 (after cycling back for 1 hour, A meets B who is still walking towards point B);
-問此時乙距B地多少公里？ (The question asks: How many kilometers is B away from point B at that moment?)
